TITLE: Russia pummels Kyiv with waves of explosive drones ahead of Ukrainian founding holiday
SUMMARY: Ukraine shot down 52 of 54 Russian "Kamikaze" drones in a massive attack against Kyiv as it prepared to celebrate its 1,541st anniversary on Sunday.

TITLE: 13-year old girl dies from 'chroming,' latest alarming social media trend
SUMMARY: The trend known as "chroming" is a new variant of the long-running trend of huffing or sniffing, this time involving aerosol cans, metallic paints and solvents.

TITLE: North Korea infant jailed for life after parents found with Bible according to recent report
SUMMARY: A U.S. State Department report found that a infant and his entire family were sentenced to a North Korean prison camp for having a Bible.

TITLE: Ontario man allegedly killed tenants in landlord-tenant dispute: Police
SUMMARY: Police in Ontario, Canada are investigating a double homicide after a man allegedly shot ad killed two people in a landlord-tenant dispute.

TITLE: Massive sea urchin die-off in Israeli gulf threatens nearby coral reefs, researchers say
SUMMARY: Coral reefs in the Red Sea near Israel may be under threat as black sea urchins, a species critical to maintaining a healthy reef habitat, are dying off at an alarming rate.

TITLE: Turkey presidential election: How will runoff affect US relationship, NATO, sale of F-16s?
SUMMARY: Election polls suggest Erdogan might continue his reign as Turkeyâ€™s longest-serving leader, and that could lead to friction with NATO and the fight against ISIS in Syria.

TITLE: Killer whales may be attacking boats as revenge for injured matriarch: scientists
SUMMARY: One female orca may have taught other adults, with younger orcas picking up the behavior from watching the adults perform these coordinated attacks on boats.

TITLE: Polish lawmakers look to investigate Russian influence in move opponents say targets ex-PM
SUMMARY: Polish lawmakers on Friday passed a bill establishing a state committee to investigate Russian influence, which critics say unfairly targets the nation's opposition leader.

TITLE: Guatemalan high court blocks presidential frontrunner's candidacy
SUMMARY: Guatemala's Constitutional Court has forcibly ended the presidential candidacy of Carlos Pineda, an independent who had been leading in polls.

TITLE: Germany denies chancellor's criticism of climate protestors incited raids
SUMMARY: German Chancellor Olaf Scholz's spokesman on Friday denied that his boss' criticism of Last Generation climate activists may have led to raids on them this week.

TITLE: English couple sentenced to life in prison for murdering baby son in case of "unimaginable cruelty"
SUMMARY: An English couple who fought to regain custody of their son from child services was sentenced to life in prison for murder after fatally abusing the 10-month-old.

TITLE: Over 30 women held hostage by Cameroonian rebels released
SUMMARY: Over 30 women abducted from the northwestern Cameroonian village of Babanki by English-speaking rebels have been released, according to government officials.

TITLE: China enters waters off of Vietnam near Russian gas block in 'worrying escalation'
SUMMARY: China on Friday again disregarded Vietnam's exclusive economic zone by deploying a research vessel near a gas block jointly operated by Hanoi and Russian firms.

TITLE: Court suspends euthanization order for bear involved in fatal attack
SUMMARY: A bear that is responsible for the death of a runner last month in Italy's Alps has been spared for now by an administrative court. The bear was found April 18 after an ongoing search.

TITLE: Italian rescuers find no trace of distressed vessel carrying 500 migrants in Mediterranean
SUMMARY: A boat carrying 500 migrants across the Mediterranean Sea that was reportedly in distress is still unaccounted for, according to Italian and Libyan authorities.

TITLE: At least 19 dead in Cameroon bus crash
SUMMARY: A passenger bus collided with a "heavy-duty" truck while en route to the southern Cameroonian town of Eseka, leaving at least 19 people dead.

TITLE: UK parents sentenced to life in prison for horrific murder of 10-month-old son on Christmas day
SUMMARY: U.K. parents convicted of killing their 10-month-old son, Finley Boden, were sentenced to life in prison for the "savage and brutal" abuse of their infant.

TITLE: Damaged yacht among 2 dozen vessels targeted by rogue orca whale pod this year
SUMMARY: A British-owned yacht immobilized by a pod of orcas has found itself the latest victim of about 35 whales known to ram boats along the Iberian Peninsula's Atlantic coast.

TITLE: 18 Belgian students found guilty in fatal initiation ritual, sentenced to community service
SUMMARY: 18 Belgian students have been found guilty Friday for their role in a fatal initiation ritual. The students were sentenced to 300 hours of community service and a 400-euro fine each.

TITLE: 6 migrant traffickers arrested after opening fire on Albanian border police
SUMMARY: Albanian police say they have arrested six migrant traffickers for allegedly organizing an illegal border crossing for people from Arab countries and opening fire on border police.

TITLE: Uyghur student missing for weeks after being interrogated by police at airport in Hong Kong
SUMMARY: A human rights group said Friday a Uyghur student in Hong Kong was reported as missing for over two weeks following a message stating that he was being questioned by Chinese authorities.

TITLE: Tragedy strikes as dinghy overturns near Greek island of Mykonos leaving 3 dead, several missing
SUMMARY: A dinghy that overturned near the Greek island of Mykonos left three people dead and several others missing. The incident in the Aegean Sea occurred early Friday.

TITLE: Clashes erupt as ethnic Serbs block municipal buildings in northern Kosovo, Serbian troops mobilized
SUMMARY: Clashes are erupting in northern Kosovo as ethnic Serbs block the entrance of municipal buildings to prevent elected officials from entering. Serbian troops have been mobilized.

TITLE: Sudan conflict: Improved adherence to cease-fire reported by Saudi Arabia and US
SUMMARY: Saudi Arabia and the United States say the warring parties in Sudan are adhering better to a week-long cease-fire after days of fighting. The two countries made a statement Friday.

TITLE: Locals in Spanish seaside destination have message for tourists: 'Go home'
SUMMARY: Locals in Barcelona are saying no more to mass tourism and are calling on officials to take counter measures as the number of visitors to the city once again surges.
